<br>
Mages are the least dependent on current mana of any caster, we <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">need</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> mana generation less than other casters, especially wizards.<br>
<br>
Reclaim a few pets, and you have the equivalent of lots of FT <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(which is why I pass up these items in favor of the other guild casters)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I can be rezzed, loot my corpse, and be at full mana, all before the rezz effects wear off.  I do not need FT.<br>
<br>
Do we need it to get into groups?  Well, barring charm, we are among the highest damage output classes, so we bring plenty to a group already.<br>
<br>
I am not sure what the magician class <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">needs</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> now, except perhaps less pinata-like pets, but summoned FT seems more like a solution in search of a problem.<br>
