<br>
1) FT is a &quot;status symbol&quot; that is meant to be difficult to obtain. You don't find FT items dropping from mobs that level 50s mages can raid. You do not get FT items from Plane of Hate or Fear (other than Cazic loot). By making FT items summonable (and therefore common), you are devaluing the efforts of those who busted their asses obtaining them.<br>
<br>
2) Adding FT is not necessarily a good thing either, considering that it's capped. For those mages near or at the cap, this change provides them with no benefit, yet they were also negatively affected by the Rod 2 nerf.<br>
<br>
